lectual investigation, while reminding us of our belonging to a common humanity, regardless of differences in our individual cultures, languages, preferences, and traditions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aPhilosophy, Chinesey20th century. 0aPhilosophy, Chinesey21st century. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Comparative Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847248540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438472485423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438472485/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles